race.comment: YOUBEEFORTY (4) found it a bit tough in town last start, but his prior form reads strongly for this level. Drops back to a more suitable trip after 25 days between runs and is expect him to be right in the finish. PRINCE LUCIFER (6) broke his maiden stylishly over this track and trip two back. Last run was below his best but he had genuine excuses, and a sharp rebound is well within reach. ARLO'S DREAM (7) is edging closer to a breakthrough, beaten only a head last start in a strong maiden. Draws well again and doesn't need to improve much to get the verdict. OLDPOP (5) was below his best last time when sent around long odds in town. This is easier, though he will need some luck from the car park draw. Keeping safe in placings.
